O'NEILL CALLS FOR STREAMLINED BORDER TRADE
The Treasury Secretary embraced a vision of trade that
would significantly expedite the movement, and reduce
the cost, of goods crossing borders.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLF0A3

IMPORTERS KEY TO SECURITY: BONNER
Customs Commissioner Robert C. Bonner asked importers
to tighten the security of their supply chains as part
of their role in preventing terrorist attacks against
the United States.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLG0A4

HUTCHISON INKS CHINA PORT EXPANSION DEAL
The port operator will help develop the largest
container facility in Shenzhen, adjacent to Hong Kong.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLH0A5

PORT OPERATOR WARNS OF BOX EXODUS IF UK PROPOSAL
 IS SCUTTLED
Britain's largest container port operator said that
the United Kingdom risks losing a large share of
container traffic to rival continental European
ports if its planned megaport isn't approved.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLI0A6

COSCO, HANJIN, SENATOR PLAN SLOT CHARTERS
The carriers plan to share space and coordinate port
calls and sailings in the trans-Pacific trade.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLJ0A7

INDIA-EUROPE LINES TALKING MERGER
Seven ocean carriers serving the trade route between
South Asia and Europe are discussing a merger of their
respective consortia.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLK0A8

MALAYSIA PORT SEES OWNERSHIP SHIFT
The fast-growing Port of Tanjung Pelepas is getting a new owner.
http://news.joc.com/cgi-bin7/flo?y=eD8A0BejkZ0BbA0SLL0AA

